				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2020 23:38:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RandomGuyWShotgun</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5269778</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think this had a pretty great punchline, I mean if you think about it in-universe it would make sense someone would try and make this. My issue is that there isn't enough buildup, This didn't really make me laugh since the punchline is basically a quarter of the article if there was a bit more buildup, like some hesitation on the foundation's part or some other vague records of it could have gone a long way. I know that if you build it up too much than the joke will feel disappointing and the audience will feel cheated, but one extra record worth of buildup would have gone a long way.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
